http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Thiruvananthapuram/Minister-promises-pay-revision-for-RTC-staff/article14000912.ece

Wage revision for KSRTC employees will be considered once the government approves the report of the Pay Commission for State government employees and teachers, Minister for Transport Thiruvanchoor Radhakrishnan has said.The Minister assured the representatives of recognised trade unions during a meeting here on Thursday that 10 per cent each of DA arrears would be given along with February and April salaries and the remaining in the gap of three months and before December. The KSRTC management had been asked to prepare guidelines for transfers in the organisation.